.TH CMT_ARCHITECTURE 3 "LIBCMT" "CMT_ARCHITECTURE" "CPU Architecture Detection"

.SH NAME
CMT_ARCHITECTURE \- Detect CPU and compiler target bit-width

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #define INCL__ARCHITECTURE
.br
.B #include <LIBCMT/LIBCMT.h>

.SH FILES
LIBCMT/ENVIRONMENTS/ARCHITECTURE.h

.SH DESCRIPTION
This header provides macros for determining the target system's architecture bit-width as detected by the compiler.

.SH MACROS
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_512_BIT__
Defined if the system supports 512-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_256_BIT__
Defined if the system supports 256-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_128_BIT__
Defined if the system supports 128-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_64_BIT__
Defined if targeting a 64-bit architecture.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_32_BIT__
Defined if targeting a 32-bit architecture.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_31_BIT__
Defined if the system supports 31-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_16_BIT__
Defined if targeting a 16-bit architecture.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_8_BIT__
Defined if targeting an 8-bit architecture.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_BIT__
Evaluates to the detected bit-width (8, 16, 32, 64, 128, or 256).

.SH DETAILS
These macros allow compile-time selection of behavior depending on the underlying CPU or compiler-targeted architecture.

.SH SEE ALSO
.B CMT_CPU(3),
.B LIBCMT(3)

